The search starts at the beginning of the list, and the index of the first matching element is returned. If no match is found then -1 is returned.       • add

        public PersistentList<E> add(E e)
        Description copied from interface: PersistentList
        Adds an element to the collection.

        This method should run in constant time, or at worst sub-linear time. It makes no guarantees as to what position the new element will occupy. It is typically either the front of the list or the end of the list.

        Use this when order of elements is less important than speed of insertion, like when using the list as an efficient "bag" (unordered collection that allows duplicates). If order does matter, then use PersistentList.addFirst(Object) or PersistentList.addLast(Object) instead.

        This method is overridden to covariantly return a PersistentList instead of a PersistentCollection.

        Specified by:
        add in interface PersistentCollection<E>
        Specified by:
        add in interface PersistentList<E>
        Parameters:
        e - the element to add
        Returns:
        a new version of the collection that includes the specified item

      • addAll

        public PersistentList<E> addAll(Iterable<? extends E> items)
        Description copied from interface: PersistentList
        Adds multiple elements to the collection.

        This method will preserve the order of the specified collection as far as their order in the returned new list. This method may insert the items at the front of the list or may instead append them at the end of the list, depending on which is more efficient.

        Use this when order of elements is less important than speed of insertion. If order does matter, then use PersistentList.addAll(int, Iterable) instead.

        This method is overridden to covariantly return a PersistentList instead of a PersistentCollection.

        Specified by:
        addAll in interface PersistentCollection<E>
        Specified by:
        addAll in interface PersistentList<E>
        Parameters:
        items - a sequence of items to add
        Returns:
        a new version of the collection that includes all of the specified items
